parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear anti-lock brake valve can cause the brake pedal to fade, leading to a loss of brake power, which can increase the risk of accidents or fires.
symptoms: the ABS warning light is on
the driver is unable to reset the ABS system
the rear anti-lock brake valve needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake rotor can cause the brake to fail, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: A loud clank is heard from the rear of the vehicle
components fall out when the brake is removed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS brakes can cause the vehicle to catch on fire, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The right front ABS brakes fail
the source of the fire is unknown.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked cylinder head can cause engine coolant or oil leaks, leading to engine overheating, damage, or failure, which can result in costly repairs, engine replacement, or even accidents.
A faulty thermostat can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, failure, or even accidents.

Tread separation can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, rollovers, and injuries or fatalities. The failure can occur without warning, making it difficult for drivers to react in time.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Filler Pipe Corrosion and Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and leakage of the fuel filler pipe can cause a fire, potentially resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: rust or corrosion on the fuel filler pipe
fuel dripping from the fuel filler pipe.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A vehicle fire can cause serious injury or death, as well as significant property damage.
symptoms: Flames or smoke coming from the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended RPM Increase with Clutch Engaged
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended increase in RPMs while the clutch is engaged can cause the vehicle to lurch or jerk, potentially leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The engine RPMs increase suddenly while the clutch pedal is pressed
the vehicle jerks or lurches forward
the air conditioner occasionally turns on by itself when the vehicle hits a bump or jerks while in motion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails to engage or disengage gears
the vehicle loses power or stalls
the vehicle experiences sudden jerking or lurching.
